rComments: I've had professor Hastings for three years, and every year she has reiterated my desire to take a course with her. Although there is a quite a bit of reading, she still cares about students, and her office is open for anyone who wants  help or just need anyone to talk to. she resembles the model professor everyone is looking for
Really captivating easy to understand lecturer

One of the best professors I've had. Incredibly clear lectures and expectations for assignments, a fair grader, and an extremely accommodating professor; she met with me last-minute before the midterm and answered last-minute questions via email before the final. I don't know many professors who would do this. Very pleasant, genuine person.

I actually learned a lot in this class. She's a good lecturer, doesn't drone on and on. The assignments are pretty straight forward and easy. Tutorials are kinda pointless imo, but mandatory so go to those. Overall, good class + good prof, you'll get a really good grade with her, she's one of the best.

Had her for Canadian History. Best professor you can get. Her lectures are clear and concise and up to point, she gives you helpful feedback on essays. finish your assignment ahead of time, and she will provide excellent feedback for improvement on your assignment. make no mistake, come to class, and you'll do fine, if not, don't expect a good mark

Had Prof. Hastings twice once for Themes in World Hist.II, and another time for Early Atlantic Canada. I found she was way better in the Early Atlantic Canada course. Even though her lectures are boring she knew exactly what was talking about, made it easy to understand. Her mid-terms, finals, and assignments are VERY basic and doable. Easy marker.

This was a bird course so it was fairly easy. Read the book (needed for the tutorial), other than that as long as you pay attention, you'll be good. She posts lots of her info on the powerpoint slides which helped with studying.
